(544, 'Kabab Chini', 'kabab-chini', '10 gm', 30, 35, 1, 14, 2, '1628627719-image-Kabab Chini 10 gm-compressed-compressed.jpg', '<p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, &quot;Droid Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;lucida grande&quot;, tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif;\">Kabab Chini, also known as cubeb or tailed pepper, is a spice derived from the dried unripe fruits of the *Piper cubeba* plant. Native to Java and Sumatra in Indonesia, it is widely cultivated in other parts of Southeast Asia, India, and Malaysia. Kabab Chini is known for its aromatic and medicinal properties and is often used in Ayurvedic medicine.</span></p>', 1, 3, '2021-08-11 00:35:19', '2026-01-21 01:18:15'),
